<subSubSection lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="64" pageId="6" pageNumber="62" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1364,2036]" pageId="6" pageNumber="62">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1364,1389]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="62" reason="1">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Black, distinctly grey pruinose; frons and face setose; ocellar tubercle with 2 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1165,1179,1364,1387]" pageId="6" pageNumber="62">–</emphasis>
3 pairs of more robust setae; scutum and scutellum with paramedian longitudinal band of grey pruinosity; fore tarsomere 1 swollen, around 1.5X wider than tibia; pterostigma at apex of costal cell; abdomen entirely grey pruinose in posterior view.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1364,2036]" pageId="6" pageNumber="62">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,377,1471,1496]" pageId="6" pageNumber="62">Re-description.</emphasis>
<typeStatus box="[386,487,1472,1496]" pageId="6" pageNumber="62">Holotype</typeStatus>
male. Body 
<quantity box="[633,722,1472,1496]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" pageId="6" pageNumber="62" unit="mm" value="5.5">5.5 mm</quantity>
; wing 6.0 mm long. Head (
<figureCitation box="[1034,1118,1472,1496]" captionStart="FIGURES 35–46" captionStartId="7.[151,261,1285,1308]" captionTargetBox="[151,1427,402,1264]" captionTargetId="figure-445@7.[151,1436,399,1270]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 35–46. Hilarempis elegans Bezzi, holotype ♂. 35, head, lateral view; 36, postcranium, posterolateral view; 37, detail of palpus, lateral view; 38, thorax, dorsal view; 39, left fore leg, posterior view; 40, left mid leg, posterior view; 41, left hind leg, anterior view; 42, terminalia before maceration, lateral view; 43, tergite 8, dorsal view; 44, terminalia, lateral view; 45, terminalia, posterior view; 46, scheme of the ejaculatory apodeme, posterior view. Abbreviations: ce = cercus, ce + b scl = cercus + bacilliform sclerite, ep = epandrium, hypd = hypandrium, ptg = postgonite; ph = phallus, ST = sternite, T = tergite. Scale bars: 35, 38, 39–41 = 1.0 mm; 36, 37, 42 = 0.5 mm; 43–45 = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5248048" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5248048/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="62">Fig. 35</figureCitation>
). Dichoptic; ommatidia subequal. Frons as wide as ocellar tubercle, 2X higher than greatest width, slightly divergent near antenna, matte black, brown pruinose in certain angles, and grey pruinose next to insertion of antenna. Frons with 7–8 slender lateroclinate setae. Face wider than frons, divergent at ventral margin, slightly higher than greatest width, grey pruinose with 8 pairs of slender proclinate setae. Ocellar tubercle distinct, matte black, brown pruinose in certain angles, with 2–3 pairs of divergent, more robust setae and short posterior pair. Postcranium (
<figureCitation box="[1039,1120,1652,1676]" captionStart="FIGURES 35–46" captionStartId="7.[151,261,1285,1308]" captionTargetBox="[151,1427,402,1264]" captionTargetId="figure-445@7.[151,1436,399,1270]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 35–46. Hilarempis elegans Bezzi, holotype ♂. 35, head, lateral view; 36, postcranium, posterolateral view; 37, detail of palpus, lateral view; 38, thorax, dorsal view; 39, left fore leg, posterior view; 40, left mid leg, posterior view; 41, left hind leg, anterior view; 42, terminalia before maceration, lateral view; 43, tergite 8, dorsal view; 44, terminalia, lateral view; 45, terminalia, posterior view; 46, scheme of the ejaculatory apodeme, posterior view. Abbreviations: ce = cercus, ce + b scl = cercus + bacilliform sclerite, ep = epandrium, hypd = hypandrium, ptg = postgonite; ph = phallus, ST = sternite, T = tergite. Scale bars: 35, 38, 39–41 = 1.0 mm; 36, 37, 42 = 0.5 mm; 43–45 = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5248048" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5248048/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="62">Fig. 36</figureCitation>
) matte black, grey pruinose, except just behind ocellar tubercle brown pruinose, distinct in posterior view; postocular setae distinctly subequal, upper occipital black, robust, lower occipital clear, slender. Inner and outer vertical setae slightly longer than postocular ones. Gena and postgena with clear slender setae. Proboscis (
<figureCitation box="[947,1031,1760,1784]" captionStart="FIGURES 35–46" captionStartId="7.[151,261,1285,1308]" captionTargetBox="[151,1427,402,1264]" captionTargetId="figure-445@7.[151,1436,399,1270]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 35–46. Hilarempis elegans Bezzi, holotype ♂. 35, head, lateral view; 36, postcranium, posterolateral view; 37, detail of palpus, lateral view; 38, thorax, dorsal view; 39, left fore leg, posterior view; 40, left mid leg, posterior view; 41, left hind leg, anterior view; 42, terminalia before maceration, lateral view; 43, tergite 8, dorsal view; 44, terminalia, lateral view; 45, terminalia, posterior view; 46, scheme of the ejaculatory apodeme, posterior view. Abbreviations: ce = cercus, ce + b scl = cercus + bacilliform sclerite, ep = epandrium, hypd = hypandrium, ptg = postgonite; ph = phallus, ST = sternite, T = tergite. Scale bars: 35, 38, 39–41 = 1.0 mm; 36, 37, 42 = 0.5 mm; 43–45 = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5248048" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5248048/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="62">Fig. 35</figureCitation>
) length less than head height, with labrum black, shiny. Palpus (
<figureCitation box="[477,559,1796,1820]" captionStart="FIGURES 35–46" captionStartId="7.[151,261,1285,1308]" captionTargetBox="[151,1427,402,1264]" captionTargetId="figure-445@7.[151,1436,399,1270]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 35–46. Hilarempis elegans Bezzi, holotype ♂. 35, head, lateral view; 36, postcranium, posterolateral view; 37, detail of palpus, lateral view; 38, thorax, dorsal view; 39, left fore leg, posterior view; 40, left mid leg, posterior view; 41, left hind leg, anterior view; 42, terminalia before maceration, lateral view; 43, tergite 8, dorsal view; 44, terminalia, lateral view; 45, terminalia, posterior view; 46, scheme of the ejaculatory apodeme, posterior view. Abbreviations: ce = cercus, ce + b scl = cercus + bacilliform sclerite, ep = epandrium, hypd = hypandrium, ptg = postgonite; ph = phallus, ST = sternite, T = tergite. Scale bars: 35, 38, 39–41 = 1.0 mm; 36, 37, 42 = 0.5 mm; 43–45 = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5248048" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5248048/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="62">Fig. 37</figureCitation>
) dark brown, with long, slender distinct setae. Antenna (
<figureCitation box="[1201,1283,1796,1820]" captionStart="FIGURES 35–46" captionStartId="7.[151,261,1285,1308]" captionTargetBox="[151,1427,402,1264]" captionTargetId="figure-445@7.[151,1436,399,1270]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 35–46. Hilarempis elegans Bezzi, holotype ♂. 35, head, lateral view; 36, postcranium, posterolateral view; 37, detail of palpus, lateral view; 38, thorax, dorsal view; 39, left fore leg, posterior view; 40, left mid leg, posterior view; 41, left hind leg, anterior view; 42, terminalia before maceration, lateral view; 43, tergite 8, dorsal view; 44, terminalia, lateral view; 45, terminalia, posterior view; 46, scheme of the ejaculatory apodeme, posterior view. Abbreviations: ce = cercus, ce + b scl = cercus + bacilliform sclerite, ep = epandrium, hypd = hypandrium, ptg = postgonite; ph = phallus, ST = sternite, T = tergite. Scale bars: 35, 38, 39–41 = 1.0 mm; 36, 37, 42 = 0.5 mm; 43–45 = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5248048" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5248048/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="62">Fig. 35</figureCitation>
) matte black, velvety, except apex of pedicel brown; postpedicel 2X length of scape and pedicel combined, and almost 3X length of apparently two-segmented stylus. Segment 1 of stylus apparently masked by segment 2, segment 2 short, around 0.5 postpedicel length and 3X longer than the rather wide segment 3.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1364,2036]" lastBlockId="7.[151,1437,151,355]" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="63" pageId="6" pageNumber="62">
Thorax (
<figureCitation box="[295,378,1940,1964]" captionStart="FIGURES 35–46" captionStartId="7.[151,261,1285,1308]" captionTargetBox="[151,1427,402,1264]" captionTargetId="figure-445@7.[151,1436,399,1270]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 35–46. Hilarempis elegans Bezzi, holotype ♂. 35, head, lateral view; 36, postcranium, posterolateral view; 37, detail of palpus, lateral view; 38, thorax, dorsal view; 39, left fore leg, posterior view; 40, left mid leg, posterior view; 41, left hind leg, anterior view; 42, terminalia before maceration, lateral view; 43, tergite 8, dorsal view; 44, terminalia, lateral view; 45, terminalia, posterior view; 46, scheme of the ejaculatory apodeme, posterior view. Abbreviations: ce = cercus, ce + b scl = cercus + bacilliform sclerite, ep = epandrium, hypd = hypandrium, ptg = postgonite; ph = phallus, ST = sternite, T = tergite. Scale bars: 35, 38, 39–41 = 1.0 mm; 36, 37, 42 = 0.5 mm; 43–45 = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5248048" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5248048/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="62">Fig. 38</figureCitation>
). Matte black, velvety; scutum with paramedian longitudinal grey pruinosity band along acrostichal rows of setae, reaching scutellum medially; grey pruinosity also present on postpronotal lobe and notopleuron, mesopleuron and postnotum, latter two with more distinct pruinosity in certain angles. Chaetotaxy: 2 antepronotals, lateral robust; about 15 slender, subequal postpronotals; 8–10 slender clear proepisternals; several slender, clear proepimerals; about 10 slender uniserial acrostichals, anteriorly more spaced, extending slightly beyond transverse suture level; about 18 slender biserial dorsocentrals, latter 2 more robust and more separated; 2 short intra-alar presuturals; 1–2 intra-alar postsuturals nearly aligned with supra-alar postsuturals; 2–3 short supraalar presuturals; 4–5 supra-alar postsuturals, last robust; 1 robust postalar; 4 robust scutellars with short intercalary setae.
</paragraph>
