<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,1505,2036]" pageId="7" pageNumber="63">
Legs (
<figureCitation box="[271,398,1505,1530]" captionStart="FIGURES 35–46" captionStartId="7.[151,261,1285,1308]" captionTargetBox="[151,1427,402,1264]" captionTargetId="figure-445@7.[151,1436,399,1270]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 35–46. Hilarempis elegans Bezzi, holotype ♂. 35, head, lateral view; 36, postcranium, posterolateral view; 37, detail of palpus, lateral view; 38, thorax, dorsal view; 39, left fore leg, posterior view; 40, left mid leg, posterior view; 41, left hind leg, anterior view; 42, terminalia before maceration, lateral view; 43, tergite 8, dorsal view; 44, terminalia, lateral view; 45, terminalia, posterior view; 46, scheme of the ejaculatory apodeme, posterior view. Abbreviations: ce = cercus, ce + b scl = cercus + bacilliform sclerite, ep = epandrium, hypd = hypandrium, ptg = postgonite; ph = phallus, ST = sternite, T = tergite. Scale bars: 35, 38, 39–41 = 1.0 mm; 36, 37, 42 = 0.5 mm; 43–45 = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5248048" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5248048/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="63">
Fig. 39 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[353,367,1506,1530]" pageId="7" pageNumber="63">–</emphasis>
41
</figureCitation>
). Black, becoming dark brown from tibiae, grey pruinose in certain angles, notably coxae, trochanter and femora. Leg setae relatively short. Fore tibia (
<figureCitation box="[851,935,1541,1565]" captionStart="FIGURES 35–46" captionStartId="7.[151,261,1285,1308]" captionTargetBox="[151,1427,402,1264]" captionTargetId="figure-445@7.[151,1436,399,1270]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 35–46. Hilarempis elegans Bezzi, holotype ♂. 35, head, lateral view; 36, postcranium, posterolateral view; 37, detail of palpus, lateral view; 38, thorax, dorsal view; 39, left fore leg, posterior view; 40, left mid leg, posterior view; 41, left hind leg, anterior view; 42, terminalia before maceration, lateral view; 43, tergite 8, dorsal view; 44, terminalia, lateral view; 45, terminalia, posterior view; 46, scheme of the ejaculatory apodeme, posterior view. Abbreviations: ce = cercus, ce + b scl = cercus + bacilliform sclerite, ep = epandrium, hypd = hypandrium, ptg = postgonite; ph = phallus, ST = sternite, T = tergite. Scale bars: 35, 38, 39–41 = 1.0 mm; 36, 37, 42 = 0.5 mm; 43–45 = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5248048" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5248048/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="63">Fig. 39</figureCitation>
) with 1 anterodorsal, 1 posterodorsal and 2 posterior setae at apex; first fore tarsomere swollen, around 1.5X wider than tibia and about.6 length of fore tibia. Mid femur (
<figureCitation box="[285,366,1613,1637]" captionStart="FIGURES 35–46" captionStartId="7.[151,261,1285,1308]" captionTargetBox="[151,1427,402,1264]" captionTargetId="figure-445@7.[151,1436,399,1270]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 35–46. Hilarempis elegans Bezzi, holotype ♂. 35, head, lateral view; 36, postcranium, posterolateral view; 37, detail of palpus, lateral view; 38, thorax, dorsal view; 39, left fore leg, posterior view; 40, left mid leg, posterior view; 41, left hind leg, anterior view; 42, terminalia before maceration, lateral view; 43, tergite 8, dorsal view; 44, terminalia, lateral view; 45, terminalia, posterior view; 46, scheme of the ejaculatory apodeme, posterior view. Abbreviations: ce = cercus, ce + b scl = cercus + bacilliform sclerite, ep = epandrium, hypd = hypandrium, ptg = postgonite; ph = phallus, ST = sternite, T = tergite. Scale bars: 35, 38, 39–41 = 1.0 mm; 36, 37, 42 = 0.5 mm; 43–45 = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5248048" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5248048/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="63">Fig. 40</figureCitation>
) with 4 inconspicuous anteroventral setae on distal half. Hind femur (
<figureCitation box="[1143,1224,1613,1637]" captionStart="FIGURES 35–46" captionStartId="7.[151,261,1285,1308]" captionTargetBox="[151,1427,402,1264]" captionTargetId="figure-445@7.[151,1436,399,1270]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 35–46. Hilarempis elegans Bezzi, holotype ♂. 35, head, lateral view; 36, postcranium, posterolateral view; 37, detail of palpus, lateral view; 38, thorax, dorsal view; 39, left fore leg, posterior view; 40, left mid leg, posterior view; 41, left hind leg, anterior view; 42, terminalia before maceration, lateral view; 43, tergite 8, dorsal view; 44, terminalia, lateral view; 45, terminalia, posterior view; 46, scheme of the ejaculatory apodeme, posterior view. Abbreviations: ce = cercus, ce + b scl = cercus + bacilliform sclerite, ep = epandrium, hypd = hypandrium, ptg = postgonite; ph = phallus, ST = sternite, T = tergite. Scale bars: 35, 38, 39–41 = 1.0 mm; 36, 37, 42 = 0.5 mm; 43–45 = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5248048" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5248048/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="63">Fig. 41</figureCitation>
) with row of small anteroventral setae at distal.75 and hind tibia with small dorsal row extending throughout length.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,1505,2036]" pageId="7" pageNumber="63">
Wing (
<figureCitation box="[277,363,1685,1709]" captionStart="FIGURES 70–75" captionStartId="12.[151,261,579,602]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,558]" captionTargetId="figure-502@12.[151,1436,193,558]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 70–75. Wings. 70, Hilarempis argentifera Bezzi, holotype ♀; 71, H. barbatula Bezzi, lectotype ♂ (pres. desig.); 72, H. carinata Bezzi, lectotype ♂ (pres. desig.); 73, H. elegans Bezzi, holotype ♂; 74, H. gymnaspis Bezzi, lectotype ♂ (pres. desig.); 75, H. xanthocera Bezzi, ♀ specimen from Peru." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5248054" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5248054/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="63">Fig. 73</figureCitation>
). Hyaline, slightly yellow; pterostigma on apex of costal cell; A 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1098,1106,1701,1715]" fontSize="6" pageId="7" pageNumber="63">1</subScript>
long, evanescent distally. A 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1428,1436,1701,1715]" fontSize="6" pageId="7" pageNumber="63">1</subScript>
almost entirely evanescent. Halter dark brown with stem partially yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,1505,2036]" pageId="7" pageNumber="63">
Abdomen matte black, velvety, entirely grey pruinose in anterior view, with clear setae longer laterally on tergites 1–3. Sternites concolorous with tergites. In natural position, apex rather vertical (
<figureCitation box="[1121,1207,1796,1820]" captionStart="FIGURES 35–46" captionStartId="7.[151,261,1285,1308]" captionTargetBox="[151,1427,402,1264]" captionTargetId="figure-445@7.[151,1436,399,1270]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 35–46. Hilarempis elegans Bezzi, holotype ♂. 35, head, lateral view; 36, postcranium, posterolateral view; 37, detail of palpus, lateral view; 38, thorax, dorsal view; 39, left fore leg, posterior view; 40, left mid leg, posterior view; 41, left hind leg, anterior view; 42, terminalia before maceration, lateral view; 43, tergite 8, dorsal view; 44, terminalia, lateral view; 45, terminalia, posterior view; 46, scheme of the ejaculatory apodeme, posterior view. Abbreviations: ce = cercus, ce + b scl = cercus + bacilliform sclerite, ep = epandrium, hypd = hypandrium, ptg = postgonite; ph = phallus, ST = sternite, T = tergite. Scale bars: 35, 38, 39–41 = 1.0 mm; 36, 37, 42 = 0.5 mm; 43–45 = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5248048" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5248048/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="63">Fig. 42</figureCitation>
). Tergite 8 (
<figureCitation box="[1345,1428,1796,1820]" captionStart="FIGURES 35–46" captionStartId="7.[151,261,1285,1308]" captionTargetBox="[151,1427,402,1264]" captionTargetId="figure-445@7.[151,1436,399,1270]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 35–46. Hilarempis elegans Bezzi, holotype ♂. 35, head, lateral view; 36, postcranium, posterolateral view; 37, detail of palpus, lateral view; 38, thorax, dorsal view; 39, left fore leg, posterior view; 40, left mid leg, posterior view; 41, left hind leg, anterior view; 42, terminalia before maceration, lateral view; 43, tergite 8, dorsal view; 44, terminalia, lateral view; 45, terminalia, posterior view; 46, scheme of the ejaculatory apodeme, posterior view. Abbreviations: ce = cercus, ce + b scl = cercus + bacilliform sclerite, ep = epandrium, hypd = hypandrium, ptg = postgonite; ph = phallus, ST = sternite, T = tergite. Scale bars: 35, 38, 39–41 = 1.0 mm; 36, 37, 42 = 0.5 mm; 43–45 = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5248048" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5248048/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="63">Fig. 43</figureCitation>
) with small posterolateral setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,1505,2036]" pageId="7" pageNumber="63">
Terminalia (
<figureCitation box="[335,472,1868,1892]" captionStart="FIGURES 35–46" captionStartId="7.[151,261,1285,1308]" captionTargetBox="[151,1427,402,1264]" captionTargetId="figure-445@7.[151,1436,399,1270]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 35–46. Hilarempis elegans Bezzi, holotype ♂. 35, head, lateral view; 36, postcranium, posterolateral view; 37, detail of palpus, lateral view; 38, thorax, dorsal view; 39, left fore leg, posterior view; 40, left mid leg, posterior view; 41, left hind leg, anterior view; 42, terminalia before maceration, lateral view; 43, tergite 8, dorsal view; 44, terminalia, lateral view; 45, terminalia, posterior view; 46, scheme of the ejaculatory apodeme, posterior view. Abbreviations: ce = cercus, ce + b scl = cercus + bacilliform sclerite, ep = epandrium, hypd = hypandrium, ptg = postgonite; ph = phallus, ST = sternite, T = tergite. Scale bars: 35, 38, 39–41 = 1.0 mm; 36, 37, 42 = 0.5 mm; 43–45 = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5248048" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5248048/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="63">Figs. 43–46</figureCitation>
). Cercus and lobe formed by cercal plate + bacilliform sclerite somewhat fused. Epandrium (
<figureCitation box="[233,366,1904,1928]" captionStart="FIGURES 35–46" captionStartId="7.[151,261,1285,1308]" captionTargetBox="[151,1427,402,1264]" captionTargetId="figure-445@7.[151,1436,399,1270]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 35–46. Hilarempis elegans Bezzi, holotype ♂. 35, head, lateral view; 36, postcranium, posterolateral view; 37, detail of palpus, lateral view; 38, thorax, dorsal view; 39, left fore leg, posterior view; 40, left mid leg, posterior view; 41, left hind leg, anterior view; 42, terminalia before maceration, lateral view; 43, tergite 8, dorsal view; 44, terminalia, lateral view; 45, terminalia, posterior view; 46, scheme of the ejaculatory apodeme, posterior view. Abbreviations: ce = cercus, ce + b scl = cercus + bacilliform sclerite, ep = epandrium, hypd = hypandrium, ptg = postgonite; ph = phallus, ST = sternite, T = tergite. Scale bars: 35, 38, 39–41 = 1.0 mm; 36, 37, 42 = 0.5 mm; 43–45 = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5248048" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5248048/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="63">Figs. 44, 45</figureCitation>
) with distinct dorsal cleft. Hypandrium (
<figureCitation box="[821,956,1904,1928]" captionStart="FIGURES 35–46" captionStartId="7.[151,261,1285,1308]" captionTargetBox="[151,1427,402,1264]" captionTargetId="figure-445@7.[151,1436,399,1270]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 35–46. Hilarempis elegans Bezzi, holotype ♂. 35, head, lateral view; 36, postcranium, posterolateral view; 37, detail of palpus, lateral view; 38, thorax, dorsal view; 39, left fore leg, posterior view; 40, left mid leg, posterior view; 41, left hind leg, anterior view; 42, terminalia before maceration, lateral view; 43, tergite 8, dorsal view; 44, terminalia, lateral view; 45, terminalia, posterior view; 46, scheme of the ejaculatory apodeme, posterior view. Abbreviations: ce = cercus, ce + b scl = cercus + bacilliform sclerite, ep = epandrium, hypd = hypandrium, ptg = postgonite; ph = phallus, ST = sternite, T = tergite. Scale bars: 35, 38, 39–41 = 1.0 mm; 36, 37, 42 = 0.5 mm; 43–45 = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5248048" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5248048/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="63">Figs. 44–45</figureCitation>
) with two median lateral projections. Postgonite sinuous. Phallus longer than postgonite apex, with short subapical setae and small apical membranous expansion. Ejaculatory apodeme tetralamellar with short lateral lamellae (
<figureCitation box="[978,1062,1976,2000]" captionStart="FIGURES 35–46" captionStartId="7.[151,261,1285,1308]" captionTargetBox="[151,1427,402,1264]" captionTargetId="figure-445@7.[151,1436,399,1270]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 35–46. Hilarempis elegans Bezzi, holotype ♂. 35, head, lateral view; 36, postcranium, posterolateral view; 37, detail of palpus, lateral view; 38, thorax, dorsal view; 39, left fore leg, posterior view; 40, left mid leg, posterior view; 41, left hind leg, anterior view; 42, terminalia before maceration, lateral view; 43, tergite 8, dorsal view; 44, terminalia, lateral view; 45, terminalia, posterior view; 46, scheme of the ejaculatory apodeme, posterior view. Abbreviations: ce = cercus, ce + b scl = cercus + bacilliform sclerite, ep = epandrium, hypd = hypandrium, ptg = postgonite; ph = phallus, ST = sternite, T = tergite. Scale bars: 35, 38, 39–41 = 1.0 mm; 36, 37, 42 = 0.5 mm; 43–45 = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5248048" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5248048/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="63">Fig. 46</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,1505,2036]" box="[199,413,2012,2036]" pageId="7" pageNumber="63">Female. Unknown.</paragraph>
